Louis G. Conforti  Chief Executive Officer & Director, Washington Prime Group Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships52$6,316,993As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Louis G. Conforti, also known as Lou, serves as the Chief Executive Officer since October 6, 2016 and Director since May 27, 2014 of Washington Prime Group Inc. and previously served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer from June 20, 2016 to October 6, 2016. Mr. Conforti brings to firm a progressive and successful career in the real estate industry, specifically in the REIT space. Previously, he served as Global Head of Strategy and Executive Director at Colony ... Capital, Inc since July 30, 2015 until July 4, 2016. Mr. Conforti served as a Senior Managing Director at Balyasny Asset Management L.P. until March 2015 and as a Real Estate Portfolio Manager from December 19, 2012 to March 2015. Previously, he served as the Global Head of Real Estate and Head of Global Property Group at UBS O'Connor LLC. Mr. Conforti was a Partner and Senior Portfolio Manager at O'Connor Colony Property Strategies. In addition, he was a Managing Director and Head of Real Estate Investments at Stark Investments LP and had also worked at The Greenwood Group. Previously, He served as a Co-President and Chief Financial Officer at Prime Group Realty Trust since June 2000 until October 2013. From November 1999 to June 2000, he served as an Executive Vice President of Capital Markets at Prime Group Realty Trust., and from June 1998 to November 1999, He served as Senior Vice President of Capital Markets at the firm. From July 1997 to May 1998, he served as an Executive Director of Real Estate Investment Banking at CIBC Oppenheimer Corp. Prior to his affiliation with the firm, he was a Vice President in the Real Estate Group of Alex Brown & Sons. During his career, He has been responsible for the completion of publicly-traded and privately-placed equity, preferred equity and commercial mortgage transactions, including commercial mortgage-backed securitizations, totaling several billion dollars as well as strategic advisory for public and private real estate companies. Prior to PGE, Mr. Conforti was an investment banker at Alex Brown & Sons and CIBC World Markets. He serves as a Director of Simon Property Group, Inc. He has been an Executive Director of Colony Capital, Inc. since July 30, 2015. He has been a Director of Washington Prime Group Inc. since May 27, 2014. He is a member of the National Association of Real Estate Investment Trusts and the Urban Land Institute. He holds a Bachelor's Degree from Lake Forest College.Read Full Background




